{"lemma":"غُلامُ","slug":"غُلامُ","root":"غ.ل.م","root_slug":"غ-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غُلام","root":"غلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":13},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32306"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8F%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a young male human, a boy-child","examples":[{"text":"يَا زَكَرِيَّا إِنَّا نُبَشِّرُكَ بِغُلَامٍ ٱسْمُهُ يَحْيَىٰ","english":"Zakariyyāh, we bring you the good news of a boy whose name shall be Yaḥyāh."},{"text":"10th century, Al-Mutanabbi\nفَرُبَّ غُلَامٍ عَلَّمَ الْمَجْدَ نَفْسَهُ كَتَعْلِيمِ سَيْفِ الدَّوْلَةِ الطَّعْنَ وٱلضَّرْبَا","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a boy-servant; a slave-boy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root غ ل م (ḡ l m). Compare Hebrew עֶלֶם (ʿélem, “a virgin boy”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32306","headword_ar":"غُلَامٌ","root":"glm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young man, youth, boy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male child:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one whose mustache is growing forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has grown"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2287},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one from the time of his birth until he attains to the period termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAb","text_ar":"شَبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young manhood"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guluwmapN","text_ar":"غُلُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN SagiyrN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ صَغِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a son that has not attained to puberty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and also applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kahol","text_ar":"كَهْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of middle age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between that age and the period when his hair has become intermixed with hoariness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, Msb, K:) Az states his having heard the Arabs call thus the new-born child and also the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kahol","text_ar":"كَهْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the female is [sometimes] termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmapN","text_ar":"غُلَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmapN","text_ar":"غُلَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in poetry, applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAriyap","text_ar":"جَارِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmN","text_ar":"غُلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilomapN","text_ar":"غِلْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) a pl. of pauc., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agolimapN","text_ar":"اَغْلِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [also a pl. of pauc.,] or of these two pls. they used only the former, (S, IAth, TA,) or some of them did so, (M, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilomaAnN","text_ar":"غِلْمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) [a pl. of mult.,] or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilomapN","text_ar":"غِلْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmN","text_ar":"غُلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulay~imN","text_ar":"غُلَيِّمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilomapN","text_ar":"غِلْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ugayolimapN","text_ar":"اُغَيْلِمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as if it were the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agolimapN","text_ar":"اَغْلِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"though [it has been said that] they did not use this last word; but some of them said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulayomapN","text_ar":"غُلَيْمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  It is also used as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male slave;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAriyapN","text_ar":"جَارِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning “ a female slave: ” ―         -b3-  and as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hireling"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"servant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","Msb","IAar","S","IAth","TA","M"]}]}}